{
  "texts": [
    "Rationale: Co-administering amiodarone with digoxin may result in increased and/or supratherapeutic serum digoxin levels due to inhibition of P-glycoprotein, increasing risk of digoxin toxicity. 15.",
    "DDI: Paxlovid / Dofetilide a.",
    "Clinical importance/relevance: Important b.",
    "Rationale: Ritonavir inhibits hepatic metabolism of dofetilide through CYP3A4, resulting in supratherapeutic plasma levels of dofetilide and increasing risk of toxicities such as QTc interval prolongation and torsades de pointe"
  ]
}